webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Party of the Eighth Mountains from above. Dominating in the picture rises the new church of the parish, consecrated on 28 June 1885. The architect Adolf Emil Melander gave the church a mark of English Gothic, a variant of neo-Gothic, which also included one of the co-architects arranged English park around the church. On the right, new church predecessors are glimpsed as ruin. The church building, of medieval origin, came to decay into the discussion of the construction or not of a new church building. Authorization to demolish it was even obtained but Lord Theodor Adelswärd intervened and commissioned the church to ruin with the maintained choir. A twenties after the time of the photo, however, a restoration of the old church would come to a stand and create a supplementary church room in the parish - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFA000034. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021018238956. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
